    • Field Detail

      • latitude

        public double latitude
        The latitude and longitude of the bus. Essentially making up its respective coordinates. This is stored as a double as latitude and longitude values are floating points numbers.

      • longitude

        public double longitude
        The latitude and longitude of the bus. Essentially making up its respective coordinates. This is stored as a double as latitude and longitude values are floating points numbers.

      • color

        public int color
        The current bus's color. This is more representative of the parentRoute its on (ie what is its parentRoute color), and thus is optional.

        This is an int instead of a Color object because for whatever reason android stores its colors as ints.

      • route

        public Route route
        The bus's corresponding route.

      • heading

        public String heading
        String used to store the buses current heading. This is optional, and may just be an empty string as a result.

      • speed

        public int speed
        Variables to store the current bus speed in mph.

      • EMPTY_BUSES

        public static final Bus[] EMPTY_BUSES
        Fallback constant in the event that we need to return an empty bus array.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Bus

        public Bus(String vehicleId,
           Route route,
           double latitude,
           double longitude)
    throws Route.RouteException
        Creates a new bus object. While the name, route, and location of the bus are required for initialization, the bus' speed and heading can be added after the fact.
        Parameters:
        vehicleId - The ID of the bus.
        route - The route object the bus belongs to. This cannot be null.
        latitude - The latitude of the bus.
        longitude - The longitude of the bus.
        Throws:
        Route.RouteException

    • Method Detail

      • getBuses

        @NonNull
public static Bus[] getBuses(JSONArray vehiclesJson)
                               throws Route.RouteException
        Creates an array of bus objects using the information in the provided json array. The size of the return array is the size of the json array.
        Parameters:
        vehiclesJson - The json array containing the bus information.
        Returns:
        An array of buses created from the information in the json array.
        Throws:
        Route.RouteException - Thrown if there are no routes to track (either MapsActivity.allRoutes is null or is 0 in length).

      • createNewBus

        @Contract(value="null -> fail")
 @NonNull
public static Bus createNewBus(JSONObject busObject)
                                                                  throws JSONException,
                                                                         Route.RouteException,
                                                                         NullPointerException
        Creates a new bus object from the information in the provided json object.
        Parameters:
        busObject - The json object containing the information to create the bus. This cannot be null.
        Returns:
        The newly created bus object.
        Throws:
        JSONException - Thrown if there was an issue parsing the json.
        Route.RouteException - Thrown if there are no routes to track (either MapsActivity.allRoutes is null or is 0 in length).
        NullPointerException - Thrown if the provided json is null.
